Weights in ANN are usually initialized with small random values before training starts.

Why Initialize Weights?

Weights decide:

How important each input is

Before learning, ANN does not know anything.

So initially:

weights are set randomly
then ANN learns and updates them during training
=======

Simple Example

Suppose ANN has 2 inputs:

X1 = Study Hours
X2 = Attendance

Initial weights may be:

W1 = 0.2
W2 = -0.1

These are random small numbers.

====

Initialize Random Weights
        ↓
Feedforward
        ↓
Calculate Error
        ↓
Backpropagation
        ↓
Update Weights
        ↓
Better Prediction

=========

